# {{.ProjectName}}

Cursor plugin scaffold generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/777genius/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.

This lane models the current observed Cursor marketplace plugin bundle shape for portable skills and shared MCP.

## Status

- Target lane: `cursor`
- Platform family: `ide_plugin`
- Launcher: not used
- Runtime claim: packaging-only plugin lane

## First Run

```bash
plugin-kit-ai generate .
plugin-kit-ai generate --check .
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform cursor --strict
```

## Target Files

- `plugin/plugin.yaml`: canonical shared plugin metadata and target list
- `plugin/skills/`: canonical portable skill authored source; `plugin-kit-ai init --extras` pre-seeds a starter and generate mirrors it into plugin-root `skills/`
- `plugin/mcp/servers.yaml`: canonical portable MCP authored source; `plugin-kit-ai init --extras` pre-seeds a starter and generate projects it into managed `.mcp.json` plus `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json#mcpServers`
- root `CLAUDE.md` and `AGENTS.md`: boundary docs that tell humans and agents to edit only `plugin/`
- `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`: generated managed Cursor plugin manifest
- `.mcp.json`: generated managed MCP sidecar when portable MCP is authored
- `skills/`: generated managed portable skills

## Current Boundary

- Supported in phase 1: portable `plugin/skills/**`, portable `plugin/mcp/servers.yaml`, and generated `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`
- Not yet modeled in this packaged lane: first-class authored Cursor `rules`, `hooks`, `commands`, or `subagents`
- Use `cursor-workspace` only when you intentionally need repo-local `.cursor/` config generation instead of a packaged plugin bundle
